  "time_ut": 1656317523,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd1\u0dc3\u0dca, \u0db6\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0dab\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9c \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc4\u0daf\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Create a road map for gas and crude oil drilling",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Parliamentary Committee on Public Accounts (COPA) has instructed the Ministry of Energy to expedite the preparation of a detailed roadmap for the exploration of gas and crude oil in Sri Lanka.",
        "The Parliamentary Committee on Public Accounts met under the chairmanship of Prof. Tissa Vitarana, Member of Parliament at the Parliament Complex recently.",
        "Officials of the Ministry of Energy briefed on the planned Natural Gas Mining Projects (LNG) in Sri Lanka and their current status.",
        "Members of Parliament asked whether the excavations required the advice of foreign governments.",
        "Responding officials have indicated that they do not need such advice from other governments.",
        "Accordingly, the COPA Committee further instructed the officials that the excavations should be completed as soon as possible.",
        "Members of Parliament Tissa Attanayake, Lasantha Alagiyawanna, Dayasiri Jayasekara, Specialist Dr. Sudarshani Fernandopulle, Udaya Gammanpila, Hesha Vithanage, Prof. Ranjith Bandara, Niroshan Perera, Mohamed Muzammil, Duminda Dissanayake, Weerasumana Weerasinghe () were present at the committee meeting. Sreetharan, B.Y.G. Ratnasekera, Ashok Abeysinghe and Prasanna Ranaweera were also present."
      ],
